description:
&lt;p&gt;Full Time Band 6 Transplant Clinical Nurse Specialist at Royal Stoke&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A rare opportunity to join the small but dynamic team of transplant specialist nurses.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role involves working with and supporting renal transplant recipients, within the outpatient setting, throughout their transplant journey, this involves working renal patients up to go onto the transplant list and caring for them post transplant.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this role you will be supported to develop skills to see patients autonomously within the clinic setting. We will welcome applications from capable and enthusiastic individuals, who have experience working in the renal/transplant setting, or have transferable skills, and want to be part of our busy, dynamic, forwarding thinking team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will need to have good communication, organisational, prioritising skills, the ability to learn and develop quickly, working autonomously and as part of a multi-disciplinary team in a busy environment. You will be expected, and supported, to undertake non medical prescribing and the health assessment modular.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please note that this Trust does not reimburse travel expenses relating to interview attendance&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Caroline Clark&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Senior Transplant Sister&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;caroline.clark@uhnm.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
